    {
      "@id": "gist:exponentOfRadian",
      "@type": "owl:DatatypeProperty",
      "rdfs:comment": [
        "DEFINITION: The exponent of radian in a product of powers of base units.",
        "EXAMPLE: In the equation '1 revolution = 6.283 x radian'\r\n\r\n\t\tthe conversion factor for revolution is 6.283\r\n\t\tthe exponent of radian is 1\r\n\t\tall other exponents are zero\r\n\r\n\t\tEvery member of a unit group containing revolution must be a multiple of radian."
      ],
      "rdfs:domain": {
        "@id": "_:ndfd66d7f0f4d459a8ec599499a65c2e2b373"
      },
      "rdfs:isDefinedBy": {
